hpnicfNqa.name: hpnicfNqa
hpnicfNqa.description: The private MIB file includes the test information of the device. It is supplementary for rfc2925.txt.

hpnicfNqaUdpEcho.name: hpnicfNqaUdpEcho
hpnicfNqaUdpEcho.description: Indicates that an implementation is using the UDP based echo server. Notes: The hpnicfNqaCtlTargetPort and hpnicfNqaCtlSourcePort need to be set, while in the pingUdpEcho Node, hpnicfNqaCtlTargetPort must be set to the default value.

hpnicfNqaTcpconnect.name: hpnicfNqaTcpconnect
hpnicfNqaTcpconnect.description: Indicates that an implementation is attempting to connect to a TCP port in order to calculate a round trip time. Notes: The hpnicfNqaCtlTargetPort and hpnicfNqaCtlSourcePort need to be set, while in the pingTcpConnectionAttempt Node, hpnicfNqaCtlTargetPort must be set to the default value.

hpnicfNqajitter.name: hpnicfNqajitter
hpnicfNqajitter.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for packet transfers. 'jitter' will cause the NQA(Network Quality Analysis) application to perform delay variance analysis.

hpnicfNqaHttp.name: hpnicfNqaHttp
hpnicfNqaHttp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for name resolution, tcp connect and tcp data transfer mechanisms for HTTP data download from a particular HTTP Server. It causes the NQA application to perform a download of the object specified in the URL.

hpnicfNqadlsw.name: hpnicfNqadlsw
hpnicfNqadlsw.description: Indicates that an implementation is using tcp for sending keepalives. 'dlsw' will cause the NQA application to perform a keepalive operation to measure the response time of a DLSw peer.

hpnicfNqadhcp.name: hpnicfNqadhcp
hpnicfNqadhcp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using udp for sending dhcp requests. 'dhcp' will cause the NQA application to perform an IP Address lease request/teardown operation.

hpnicfNqaftp.name: hpnicfNqaftp
hpnicfNqaftp.description: Indicates that an implementation is using tcp packet for ftp connect and data transfer.

hpnicfNqaMIBVersion.name: hpnicfNqaMIBVersion
hpnicfNqaMIBVersion.description: Version string of this MIB. The format will be: 'Version.Release.Patch: Description' An instance likes: '1.0.0: Initial NQA MIB'

hpnicfNqaCtlTable.name: hpnicfNqaCtlTable
hpnicfNqaCtlTable.description: Defines the NQA Control Extend Table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of performing network analysis operations at a remote host.

hpnicfNqaCtlEntry.name: hpnicfNqaCtlEntry
hpnicfNqaCtlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hpnicfNqaCtlTable. The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

hpnicfNqaCtlTargetPort.name: hpnicfNqaCtlTargetPort
hpnicfNqaCtlTargetPort.description: The destination port that may be used by udpEcho, tcpConnect and jitter probes.

hpnicfNqaCtlSourcePort.name: hpnicfNqaCtlSourcePort
hpnicfNqaCtlSourcePort.description: The source port that may be used by all tests except for dns and dlsw. If no source port is specified, system will create a random port as source port.

hpnicfNqaCtlTTL.name: hpnicfNqaCtlTTL
hpnicfNqaCtlTTL.description: Specifies the value to store in the TTL Field in the IP packet used to encapsulate the NQA probe.

hpnicfNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval.name: hpnicfNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval
hpnicfNqaCtlJitterAdminInterval.description: Time value in milliseconds that is an interval between two continuous probes in jitter test. This object is only used by jitter test.

hpnicfNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets.name: hpnicfNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets
hpnicfNqaCtlJitterAdminNumPackets.description: Packet number that specifys how many packets will be sent in one jitter test. This object is only used by jitter test.

hpnicfNqaCtlHttpOperationType.name: hpnicfNqaCtlHttpOperationType
hpnicfNqaCtlHttpOperationType.description: Http operation type: get, post or raw.

hpnicfNqaCtlHttpOperationString.name: hpnicfNqaCtlHttpOperationString
hpnicfNqaCtlHttpOperationString.description: Http operation string. For example, if the http operation type is get, the string will be url, home page and http version.

hpnicfNqaCtlFtpOperationString.name: hpnicfNqaCtlFtpOperationString
hpnicfNqaCtlFtpOperationString.description: Ftp operation string. If the ftp operation type is get, the string must be the file name which will be gotten from ftp server.

hpnicfNqaCtlVPNInstance.name: hpnicfNqaCtlVPNInstance
hpnicfNqaCtlVPNInstance.description: VPN name by which system finds route in the specified VPN to send NQA probe packets.

hpnicfNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime.name: hpnicfNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime
hpnicfNqaCtlHistoryKeptTime.description: To indicate how long the history records will be saved in the pingProbeHistoryTable table after the test stopped.

hpnicfNqaCtlHistoryEnable.name: hpnicfNqaCtlHistoryEnable
hpnicfNqaCtlHistoryEnable.description: To indicate whether the history should be recorded in the PingProbeHistoryTable or not. enabled(1) --history will be recorded disabled(2) --history will not be recorded.

hpnicfNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor.name: hpnicfNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor
hpnicfNqaCtlICPIFAdvFactor.description: The advantage factor depends on the type of access and how the service is to be used. This object will be used while calculating the ICPIF (Calculated Planning Impairment Factor) values. This is applicable only for the jitter probe. Suggestion values: |-----------------------------------|-------| | Service |factor | |-----------------------------------|-------| |conventional wire-line | 0 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |mobility within Building | 5 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |mobility within geographical area | 10 | |-----------------------------------|-------| |access to hard-to-reach location | 20 | |-----------------------------------|-------|

hpnicfNqaCtlCodecType.name: hpnicfNqaCtlCodecType
hpnicfNqaCtlCodecType.description: To indicate the codec type to be used with jitter probe. This is applicable only for the jitter probe.

hpnicfNqaResultsTable.name: hpnicfNqaResultsTable
hpnicfNqaResultsTable.description: Defines the NQA Results Extend Table for providing the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The results of these operations are stored in the hpnicfNqaResultsTable. The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

hpnicfNqaResultsEntry.name: hpnicfNqaResultsEntry
hpnicfNqaResultsEntry.description: The operation of this table is same as that of pingResultsTable.

hpnicfNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects.name: hpnicfNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects
hpnicfNqaResultsRttNumDisconnects.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the destination became disconnected. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

hpnicfNqaResultsRttTimeouts.name: hpnicfNqaResultsRttTimeouts
hpnicfNqaResultsRttTimeouts.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe timed out.

hpnicfNqaResultsRttBusies.name: hpnicfNqaResultsRttBusies
hpnicfNqaResultsRttBusies.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because all NQA tasks have been running. If a new probe fails to start, the value of this object is incremented. The next test will not start until the next Frequency.

hpnicfNqaResultsRttNoConnections.name: hpnicfNqaResultsRttNoConnections
hpnicfNqaResultsRttNoConnections.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe destination is unavailable. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

hpnicfNqaResultsRttDrops.name: hpnicfNqaResultsRttDrops
hpnicfNqaResultsRttDrops.description: The number of times that a NQA operation failed to initiated for unavailibility of necessary internal resources.

hpnicfNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors.name: hpnicfNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors
hpnicfNqaResultsRttSequenceErrors.description: The number of packets arrived out of sequence.

hpnicfNqaResultsRttStatsErrors.name: hpnicfNqaResultsRttStatsErrors
hpnicfNqaResultsRttStatsErrors.description: The number of some other errors.

hpnicfNqaResultsMaxDelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaResultsMaxDelaySD
hpnicfNqaResultsMaxDelaySD.description: The maximal delay from source device to destination device. Currently this value is only used for jitter test, and this value must be 0 in other type test. In jitter test, if destination system time is not valid, the SD delay may be set 0.

hpnicfNqaResultsMaxDelayDS.name: hpnicfNqaResultsMaxDelayDS
hpnicfNqaResultsMaxDelayDS.description: The maximal delay from destination device to source device. Currently this value is only used for jitter test, and this value is 0 in other type test. In jitter test, if destination system time is not valid, the DS delay may be set 0.

hpnicfNqaResultsLostPacketRatio.name: hpnicfNqaResultsLostPacketRatio
hpnicfNqaResultsLostPacketRatio.description: The value of this object reflects the drop rate of NQA test. For example, this value is 30 that means source device only had received 70% packets of total sent packets.

hpnicfNqaResultsPacketLateArrival.name: hpnicfNqaResultsPacketLateArrival
hpnicfNqaResultsPacketLateArrival.description: The value of this object indicates the number of the packets that arrived after the timeout.

hpnicfNqaResultsRttSum.name: hpnicfNqaResultsRttSum
hpnicfNqaResultsRttSum.description: The sum of round trip time.

hpnicfNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD
hpnicfNqaResultsNumOfDelaySD.description: The number of delay from source to destination that are successfully measured.

hpnicfNqaResultsMinDelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaResultsMinDelaySD
hpnicfNqaResultsMinDelaySD.description: The minimum of all one way times from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaResultsSumDelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaResultsSumDelaySD
hpnicfNqaResultsSumDelaySD.description: The sum of one way times from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaResultsSum2DelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaResultsSum2DelaySD
hpnicfNqaResultsSum2DelaySD.description: The sum of squares of one way times from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS.name: hpnicfNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS
hpnicfNqaResultsNumOfDelayDS.description: The number of delay from destination to source that are successfully measured.

hpnicfNqaResultsMinDelayDS.name: hpnicfNqaResultsMinDelayDS
hpnicfNqaResultsMinDelayDS.description: The minimum of all one way times from destination to source.

hpnicfNqaResultsSumDelayDS.name: hpnicfNqaResultsSumDelayDS
hpnicfNqaResultsSumDelayDS.description: The sum of one way times from destination to source.

hpnicfNqaResultsSum2DelayDS.name: hpnicfNqaResultsSum2DelayDS
hpnicfNqaResultsSum2DelayDS.description: The sum of squares of one way times from destination to source.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsTable.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsTable
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsTable.description: Statistics table for latest jitter activity.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsEntry.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsEntry
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsEntry.description: An entry contains the statistics for the latest jitter activity. This entry is created only if the pingCtlType is hpnicfNqajitter.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfRTT.description: The number of received destination device responses with which jitter test can reach round-trip time.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the minimal positive jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesSD.description: The number that records positive jitter times from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of the value of all positive jitters in packets sent from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of positive jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the minimal absolute values of negative jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the maximal absolute values of negative jitter value from source to destination in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesSD.description: The number that records negative jitter times from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of all negative jitter values in packets sent from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of negative jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test. The total number of the value of all negative jitters in packets sent from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of negative jitter values from source to destination in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the minimal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal positive jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfPositivesDS.description: The number that records positive jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfPositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of positive jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2PositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of positive jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMinOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the minimal absolute values of negative jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsMaxOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the maximal absolute values of negative jitter value from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsNumOfNegativesDS.description: The number that records negative jitter times from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSumOfNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of negative jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsSum2NegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the sum of square of negative jitter values from destination to source in the jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPacketLossSD.description: The lost packets number sent from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPacketLossDS.description: The lost packets number sent from destination to source.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesSD.description: The value of time that records the average positive jitter value from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesSD.description: The value of time that records the average negative jitter value from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAvePositivesDS.description: The value of time that records the average positive jitter value from destination to source.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsAveNegativesDS.description: The value of time that records the average negative jitter value from destination to source.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsPktLossUnknown.description: The number of packets which is lost with unknown reason.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsOperOfICPIF.description: The ICPIF (Calculated Planning Impairment Factor) value for the latest jitter test.

hpnicfNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS.name: hpnicfNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS
hpnicfNqaJitterStatsOperOfMOS.description: The MOS (Mean Opinion Score) value for the latest jitter test.

hpnicfNqaTcpServerTable.name: hpnicfNqaTcpServerTable
hpnicfNqaTcpServerTable.description: A table which contains the status of NQA tcp server configuration information.

hpnicfNqaTcpServerEntry.name: hpnicfNqaTcpServerEntry
hpnicfNqaTcpServerEntry.description: A table which contains the status of NQA tcp server configuration information. This entry includes not only the tcp server ip address but also the tcp server port.

hpnicfNqaTcpServerRowStatus.name: hpnicfNqaTcpServerRowStatus
hpnicfNqaTcpServerRowStatus.description: hpnicfNqaTcpServerIpAddress and hpnicfNqaTcpServerPort must be set during a creation operation.

hpnicfNqaUdpServerTable.name: hpnicfNqaUdpServerTable
hpnicfNqaUdpServerTable.description: Status of NQA udp server configuration information.

hpnicfNqaUdpServerEntry.name: hpnicfNqaUdpServerEntry
hpnicfNqaUdpServerEntry.description: This entry includes not only the udp server ip address but also the udp server udp port.

hpnicfNqaUdpServerRowStatus.name: hpnicfNqaUdpServerRowStatus
hpnicfNqaUdpServerRowStatus.description: hpnicfNqaUdpServerIpAddress and hpnicfNqaUdpServerPort must be set during a creation operation.

hpnicfNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.name: hpnicfNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber
hpnicfNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.description: The maximum number saved per group. The maximum value of hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber can not exceed the value of this object.

hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlTable.name: hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlTable
hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlTable.description: Defines the NQA statistics control table for providing, via SNMP, the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The results of these operations are stored in the hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsTable and the hpnicfNqaGroupStatsJitterTable.

hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlEntry.name: hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlEntry
hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlTable. The hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlTable has the same index as the pingCtlTable in order for a hpnicfNqaStatisticsCtlTable to correspond to the pingCtlEntry.

hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.name: hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsInterval
hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.description: Statistic information will be calculated after the time that is the value of hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsInterval.

hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber.name: hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber
hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsGroupNumber.description: The value of this object indicates the number of group saved. The length of this object is from 1 to hpnicfNqaStatsMaxGroupNumber.

hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime.name: hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime
hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsKeptTime.description: To indicate how long the statistic information will be saved after the test stops.

hpnicfNqaCtlBeginTime.name: hpnicfNqaCtlBeginTime
hpnicfNqaCtlBeginTime.description: Time at which the type-specified test will start.

hpnicfNqaCtlLifeTime.name: hpnicfNqaCtlLifeTime
hpnicfNqaCtlLifeTime.description: To indicate how long the type-specified test will last.

hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsTable.name: hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsTable
hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsTable.description: Defines the NQA statistics results table for providing the capability of performing NQA operations at a remote host. The statistics results of these operations in a statistic cycle are stored in the hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The statistic cycle is the value of hpnicfNqaCtlStatisticsInterval. The first two index identify the pingCtlEntry that the probe statistics result (HpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsEntry) belongs to.

hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsEntry.name: hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsEntry
hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsTable has the same index as the pingCtlTable in order for a hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsEntry to correspond to the pingCtlEntry that caused it to be created.

hpnicfNqaStatResIndex.name: hpnicfNqaStatResIndex
hpnicfNqaStatResIndex.description: An entry in this table is created when the statistics result of a NQA probe is determined. An implementation MUST start assigning hpnicfNqaStatResIndex values at 1 and wrap after exceeding the maximum possible value as defined by the limit of this object ('ffffffff'h).

hpnicfNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType.name: hpnicfNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType
hpnicfNqaStatResIpTargetAddressType.description: This object indicates the type of address stored in the corresponding hpnicfNqaStatResIpTargetAddress object.

hpnicfNqaStatResIpTargetAddress.name: hpnicfNqaStatResIpTargetAddress
hpnicfNqaStatResIpTargetAddress.description: This object represent the host address to be used at a remote host for performing a network analysis operation.

hpnicfNqaStatResMinRtt.name: hpnicfNqaStatResMinRtt
hpnicfNqaStatResMinRtt.description: The minimum NQA probe round-trip-time (RTT) received. The value of 0 for this object implies that no RTT has been received.

hpnicfNqaStatResMaxRtt.name: hpnicfNqaStatResMaxRtt
hpnicfNqaStatResMaxRtt.description: The maximum NQA probe round-trip-time (RTT) received. The value of 0 for this object implies that no RTT has been received.

hpnicfNqaStatResProbeResponses.name: hpnicfNqaStatResProbeResponses
hpnicfNqaStatResProbeResponses.description: The number of responses received. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probe responses have been received.

hpnicfNqaStatResSentProbes.name: hpnicfNqaStatResSentProbes
hpnicfNqaStatResSentProbes.description: The value of this object reflects the number of probes sent. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no probes have been sent.

hpnicfNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares.name: hpnicfNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares
hpnicfNqaStatResRttSumOfSquares.description: This object contains the sum of the squares for all NQA responses received. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no NQA responses have been received.

hpnicfNqaStatResStartTime.name: hpnicfNqaStatResStartTime
hpnicfNqaStatResStartTime.description: This object contains the start time of the statistic.

hpnicfNqaStatResInterval.name: hpnicfNqaStatResInterval
hpnicfNqaStatResInterval.description: This object contains the interval between two times of statistic.

hpnicfNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects.name: hpnicfNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects
hpnicfNqaStatResRttNumDisconnects.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the destination became disconnected. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

hpnicfNqaStatResRttTimeouts.name: hpnicfNqaStatResRttTimeouts
hpnicfNqaStatResRttTimeouts.description: The number of times that a probe failed because the probe timed out.

hpnicfNqaStatResRttBusies.name: hpnicfNqaStatResRttBusies
hpnicfNqaStatResRttBusies.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because errors related to sockets.

hpnicfNqaStatResRttNoConnections.name: hpnicfNqaStatResRttNoConnections
hpnicfNqaStatResRttNoConnections.description: The number of times that a NQA probe failed because the probe destination is unavailable. For connectionless protocol pingCtlTypes, this number should be zero.

hpnicfNqaStatResRttDrops.name: hpnicfNqaStatResRttDrops
hpnicfNqaStatResRttDrops.description: The number of times that a NQA operation failed to initiate for unavailibility of necessary internal resources.

hpnicfNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors.name: hpnicfNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors
hpnicfNqaStatResRttSequenceErrors.description: The number of packets arrived out of sequence.

hpnicfNqaStatResLostPacketRatio.name: hpnicfNqaStatResLostPacketRatio
hpnicfNqaStatResLostPacketRatio.description: The value of this object reflects the drop rate of NQA test packet. For example, if the value is 30, that means source device only had received 70 percent packets of total sent packets.

hpnicfNqaStatResPacketLateArrival.name: hpnicfNqaStatResPacketLateArrival
hpnicfNqaStatResPacketLateArrival.description: The value of this object reflects the number of the packets that arrived after the timeout.

hpnicfNqaStatResRttSum.name: hpnicfNqaStatResRttSum
hpnicfNqaStatResRttSum.description: This object contains the sum of the squares for all NQA responses received during the test lifetime. The value of this object MUST be reported as 0 when no NQA responses have been received.

hpnicfNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD
hpnicfNqaStatResNumOfDelaySD.description: The number of one way times from source to destination that are successfully measured.

hpnicfNqaStatResMinDelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaStatResMinDelaySD
hpnicfNqaStatResMinDelaySD.description: The minimum one way times from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaStatResMaxDelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaStatResMaxDelaySD
hpnicfNqaStatResMaxDelaySD.description: The maximum one way times from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaStatResSumDelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaStatResSumDelaySD
hpnicfNqaStatResSumDelaySD.description: The sum of one way times from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaStatResSum2DelaySD.name: hpnicfNqaStatResSum2DelaySD
hpnicfNqaStatResSum2DelaySD.description: The sum of squares of one way times from source to destination.

hpnicfNqaStatResNumOfDelayDS.name: hpnicfNqaStatResNumOfDelayDS

hpnicfNqaReactionTable.name: hpnicfNqaReactionTable
hpnicfNqaReactionTable.description: A table of NQA test monitoring notification and reaction configuration definitions. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding pingCtlEntry is deleted.

hpnicfNqaReactionEntry.name: hpnicfNqaReactionEntry
hpnicfNqaReactionEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hpnicfNqaReactionTable. The first two index elements identify the pingCtlEntry that a hpnicfNqaReactItemIndex belongs to. The third index element selects a single reaction.

hpnicfNqaReactOwnerIndex.name: hpnicfNqaReactOwnerIndex
hpnicfNqaReactOwnerIndex.description: The first index of hpnicfNqaReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlOwnerIndex in pingCtlTable. hpnicfNqaReactOwnerIndex and hpnicfNqaReactTestName identify an existed test.

hpnicfNqaReactTestName.name: hpnicfNqaReactTestName
hpnicfNqaReactTestName.description: The second index of hpnicfNqaReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlTestName in pingCtlTable. hpnicfNqaReactOwnerIndex and hpnicfNqaReactTestName identify an existed test.

hpnicfNqaReactItemIndex.name: hpnicfNqaReactItemIndex
hpnicfNqaReactItemIndex.description: The third index of hpnicfNqaReactionTable, it definitely identifies one of the reaction configurations for a test.

hpnicfNqaReactCheckedElement.name: hpnicfNqaReactCheckedElement
hpnicfNqaReactCheckedElement.description: A list of reaction condition type. 'probetime' and 'probefailure' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is not hpnicfNqajitter. 'jitterOwdSD': one way time from source to destination in jitter test. 'jitterOwdDS': one way time from destination to source in jitter test. 'jitterrtt', 'jitterpacketloss', 'jittersd', 'jitterds', 'jitterOwdSD' and 'jitterOwdDS' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is hpnicfNqajitter. 'icpif' and 'mos' are valid when pingCtlType of the test is hpnicfNqajitter and hpnicfNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.

hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit.name: hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit
hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit.description: This object defines an administrative upper-threshold value for hpnicfNqaReactCheckedElement. The value of this object is zero if hpnicfNqaReactCheckedElement is specified as 'jitterpacketloss' and 'probefailure'.

hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit.name: hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit
hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit.description: This object defines an administrative lower-threshold value for hpnicfNqaReactCheckedElement. The value of hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit should be equal or less than the value of hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. The value of this object is zero if hpnicfNqaReactCheckedElement is specified as 'jitterpacketloss' and 'probefailure'.

hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType.name: hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType
hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType.description: This object defines the reaction threshold types. invalid(0): Invalid value. average(1): If reaction threshold type is average and the average value of watched operation exceeds threshold limit, an action specified in hpnicfNqaReactActionType is generated when hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. consecutive(2): If reaction threshold type is consecutive and the times of watched operation consecutively exceeds the limit specified by hpnicfNqaReactThresholdConsecNum, an action specified in hpnicfNqaReactActionType is generated when hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. accumulative(3): If reaction threshold type is accumulative and the times of watched operation accumulatively exceeds the limit specified by hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum, an action specified in hpnicfNqaReactActionType is generated when hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. If reaction threshold type is not configured, the value of this object is 'invalid'.

hpnicfNqaReactThresholdConsecNum.name: hpnicfNqaReactThresholdConsecNum
hpnicfNqaReactThresholdConsecNum.description: This object defines a consecutive threshold limit. The value is zero when hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is not 'consecutive'.

hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum.name: hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum
hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum.description: This object defines an accumulative threshold limit. The value is zero when the hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is not 'accumulative'.

hpnicfNqaReactActionType.name: hpnicfNqaReactActionType
hpnicfNqaReactActionType.description: Specifies the type of reaction to generate if the specified violation type occurs for the monitored element: none - No reaction is generated trapOnly - A trap is generated triggerOnly - All trigger actions defined for this entry are generated trapAndTrigger - Both a trap and all trigger actions are generated

hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus.name: hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus
hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus.description: Specifies the current status of this reaction entry: invalid - The status of the reaction entry is unknown. overThreshold - The status of the reaction entry is overThreshold when the monitored result exceeds the threshold value for the hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType. belowThreshold - The status of the reaction entry is belowThreshold when the monitored result is under the threshold value for the hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType.

hpnicfNqaReactRowStatus.name: hpnicfNqaReactRowStatus
hpnicfNqaReactRowStatus.reference: See definition of RowStatus in RFC 2579, 'Textual Conventions for SMIv2.'
hpnicfNqaReactRowStatus.description: This object allows entries to be created and deleted in the hpnicfNqaReactionTable. Creation of an entry in this table results in a new set of reaction configurations which take effect immediately. Deletion of an entry in this table results in corresponding reaction configurations are being deleted and stop taking effect.

hpnicfNqaReactCheckedNum.name: hpnicfNqaReactCheckedNum
hpnicfNqaReactCheckedNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are monitored.

hpnicfNqaReactThresholdNum.name: hpnicfNqaReactThresholdNum
hpnicfNqaReactThresholdNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are over threshold.

hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionTable.name: hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionTable
hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionTable.description: A table of NQA test monitoring notification and reaction configuration definitions. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding pingCtlEntry is deleted.

hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionEntry.name: hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionEntry
hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionEntry.description: Defines an entry in the hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionTable. The first two index elements identify the pingCtlEntry that a hpnicfNqaReactItemIndex belongs to. The third index element identifies an entry in the hpnicfNqaStatisticsResultsTable. The forth index element selects a single reaction.

hpnicfNqaStatReactOwnerIndex.name: hpnicfNqaStatReactOwnerIndex
hpnicfNqaStatReactOwnerIndex.description: The first index of hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlOwnerIndex in pingCtlTable.

hpnicfNqaStatReactTestName.name: hpnicfNqaStatReactTestName
hpnicfNqaStatReactTestName.description: The second index of hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it is the same as pingCtlTestName in pingCtlTable.

hpnicfNqaStatReactIndex.name: hpnicfNqaStatReactIndex
hpnicfNqaStatReactIndex.description: The third index of hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionTable. An entry in this table is created when the statistics result of a NQA probe is determined. An implementation MUST start assigning hpnicfNqaStatResIndex values at 1 and wrap after exceeding the maximum possible value as defined by the limit of this object ('ffffffff'h).

hpnicfNqaStatReactItemIndex.name: hpnicfNqaStatReactItemIndex
hpnicfNqaStatReactItemIndex.description: The forth index of hpnicfNqaStatisticsReactionTable, it definitely identifies one of the reaction configurations for a test

hpnicfNqaStatReactCheckedNum.name: hpnicfNqaStatReactCheckedNum
hpnicfNqaStatReactCheckedNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are monitored.

hpnicfNqaStatReactThresholdNum.name: hpnicfNqaStatReactThresholdNum
hpnicfNqaStatReactThresholdNum.description: The number of checked element samples that are over threshold.

hpnicfNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold.name: hpnicfNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold
hpnicfNqaProbeTimeOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. Probe time(equals to RTT for some type of tests) is not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. 2. The probe time is accumulatively not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum. 3. The probe time is consecutively in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hpnicfNqaReactThresholdConsecNum. This notification is valid only when hpnicfNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is not hpnicfNqajitter.

hpnicfNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold.name: hpnicfNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold
hpnicfNqaJitterRTTOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average NQA round-trip-time (RTT) of jitter packets is not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. 2. The RTT of jitter packets is accumulatively not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test. This notification is valid only when hpnicfNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is hpnicfNqajitter.

hpnicfNqaProbeFailure.name: hpnicfNqaProbeFailure
hpnicfNqaProbeFailure.description: It is generated when the value of hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the probe test accumulatively failed for a number of times specified in hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test while the value of hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is 'accumulative'. 2. When the probe test consecutively failed for a number of times specified in hpnicfNqaReactThresholdConsecNum in one test while the value of hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is 'consecutive'. This notification is valid only when hpnicfNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is not hpnicfNqajitter.

hpnicfNqaJitterPacketLoss.name: hpnicfNqaJitterPacketLoss
hpnicfNqaJitterPacketLoss.description: It is generated when the value of hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the jitter packets accumulatively lost for a number of times specified in hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum in one test while the value of hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is 'accumulative'. This notification is valid only when hpnicfNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is hpnicfNqajitter.

hpnicfNqaJitterSDOverThreshold.name: hpnicfNqaJitterSDOverThreshold
hpnicfNqaJitterSDOverThreshold.description: The SD means the jitter values from source to destination. It is generated when the value of hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average of SD in one jitter test is not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit and the hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'average' type. 2. The average of SD in one jitter test is accumulatively not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum and the hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'accumulative' type. This notification is valid only when hpnicfNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is hpnicfNqajitter.

hpnicfNqaJitterDSOverThreshold.name: hpnicfNqaJitterDSOverThreshold
hpnicfNqaJitterDSOverThreshold.description: The DS means the jitter values from destination to source. It is generated when the value of hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. The average of DS in one jitter test is not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit and the hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'average' type. 2. The average of DS in one jitter test is accumulatively not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit for a number of times specified in hpnicfNqaReactThresholdAccumNum and the hpnicfNqaReactThresholdType is specified as 'accumulative' type. This notification is valid only when hpnicfNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger' and pingCtlType of the test is hpnicfNqajitter.

hpnicfNqaICPIFOverThreshold.name: hpnicfNqaICPIFOverThreshold
hpnicfNqaICPIFOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the ICPIF value in one jitter test is not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. This notification is valid only when hpnicfNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger', pingCtlType of the test is hpnicfNqajitter and hpnicfNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.

hpnicfNqaMOSOverThreshold.name: hpnicfNqaMOSOverThreshold
hpnicfNqaMOSOverThreshold.description: It is generated when the value of hpnicfNqaReactCurrentStatus changes. The change may occur when the watched condition is over threshold or below threshold. The over threshold situations is specified as below. 1. When the MOS value in one jitter test is not in the range hpnicfNqaReactThresholdLowerLimit through hpnicfNqaReactThresholdUpperLimit. This notification is valid only when hpnicfNqaReactActionType is 'trapOnly' or 'trapAndTrigger', pingCtlType of the test is hpnicfNqajitter and hpnicfNqaCtlCodecType is 'g711Alaw' or 'g711Ulaw' or 'g729A'.
